workflow.name: Process & catalog dress images with GPT-4o, Cloudinary, and Google Sheets
workflow.description:
## Description¬†
Automate dress image handling end-to-end: search files, download them, upload to Cloudinary, invoke Azure OpenAI (GPT-4o), parse structured output, and append rows to a sheet. Gain a repeatable, low-touch process for product media and metadata logging. ‚ú®

## What This Template Does¬†
- Searches files and folders from your connected storage. üîé
- Loops over each item to process them individually. üîÅ
- Downloads each file for processing. ‚¨á
- Uploads image frames to Cloudinary via REST POST. ‚òÅÔ∏è
- Sends content to Azure OpenAI Chat Model and parses structured output. ü§ñ
- Appends rows to a sheet (two destinations supported) for logging. üìÑ
- Merges inputs where needed to streamline final outputs. üîó

## Key Benefits¬†
- Saves time by automating multi-step media handling. ‚è±
- Ensures consistent uploads and logs for every file. ‚úÖ
- Adds AI-powered processing via Azure OpenAI when needed. üß†
- Keeps records up to date with automatic sheet appends. üìà
- Modular flow that‚Äôs easy to adapt to your source/destination. üß©

## Features¬†
- File and folder search node for flexible intake. üìÇ
- Item-by-item loop for reliable, scalable processing. üîÅ
- Cloudinary image upload via HTTP POST endpoint. ‚òÅ
- Azure OpenAI Chat Model invocation. ü§ñ
- Structured Output Parser for clean, machine-readable results. üßæ
- Dual sheet append capability for separate logs. ‚ûï

## Requirements¬†
- An n8n instance (cloud or self-hosted). üß≠
- Cloudinary account with an accessible upload endpoint. ‚òÅÔ∏è
- Azure OpenAI access with a deployed Chat Model (GPT-4o). üîê
- A connected spreadsheet integration in n8n for appending rows. üìÑ
- Access to your file storage where the search and download occur. üìÇ

## Target Audience¬†
- E-commerce and catalog teams managing product media. üõçÔ∏è
- Ops teams standardizing uploads and record-keeping. üß∞
- No-code/low-code builders organizing image pipelines. üß±
- Agencies maintaining client product image workflows. üè∑Ô∏è

## Step-by-Step Setup Instructions
- Connect your file storage credential for Search/Download nodes. üîå
- Configure Cloudinary upload endpoint and credentials in n8n. ‚òÅÔ∏è
- Add Azure OpenAI credentials and set your GPT-4o deployment details. ü§ñ
- Connect your sheet credential(s) and select target sheet(s). üìÑ
- Import the workflow, assign credentials to each node, and replace placeholders. ‚úÖ
- Run once to test; then enable scheduling or triggers as needed. üöÄ
